        <p class="break" data-ng-non-bindable="">
            Looking for back/front-end dev to create a simply LAMP app, specifically, a method to measure the mood of people who enter a building. <br>
            <br>
            Overall specification:<br>
            * To be used at multiple buildings; therefore, a way of selecting a particular building to operate at (e.g., <a href="http%3A%2F%2Fapp.com%2Fbuilding_name%2F" target="_blank">http://app.com/building_name/</a> ) should be utilized both for URL and data structure. A list of buildings will be provided at time of dev.<br>
            * To show on both standard displays and accessible via mobile web. Should scale accordingly.<br>
            <br>
            Component 1: Touch display<br>
            * As a user, I want to click on a location on a display ( see: <img src="/web/images/Mood%20Meter%20Coloured.jpg"> ) or a simplified example at <<img src="/web/images/1200x630bf.jpg"> . The X axis is measured as "pleasantness" and the Y axis is measured as "energy level."<br>
            * As a user, when I click on a location on the display, I want to see a visual confirmation that I have clicked there. The display should be created using CSS+JS, and not an image.<br>
            * As a user, when I click on the display, I want the location of my click to be saved in a database, along with date-time<br>
            * As a user, when I click on the display, I want the screen to fade, and then count down (in big numbers) until a refreshed display shows - ready for the next user<br>
            <br>
            Component 2: Administrative report<br>
            * As an admin, I want to access an admin back-end<br>
            * As an admin, I want to see two reports: a report for today, and a report for "all time"<br>
            * As an admin, I want to see the report for "today." This is a visual depiction of how all the people who have clicked on the display are feeling today (an aggregate), shown the same way the grid is shown. Only "today" should show, e.g., not data from the day prior.<br>
            * As an admin, I want to see a report for "all time" that shows two graphs: one for pleasantness, and the other for energy level.
        </p>



